v1.02 ========================================================================================================
02/07/2025 
    - Starting on work for v1.02
    - Reformatted CHANGELOG to be a little more organized between dates, changes, and versions
    - Removed my broken Dijkstra cooridor generation, but keeping priority queue for now. I may come back to 
      this in the future, but for now I'm just getting it out of my way.
    - fixed (maybe?) room generation bug where size was not being recorded correctly
02/08/2025
    - Changed room creation method to generate room to a specified size; randomization is now done outside the 
      method, before it is called. This makes reading/saving rooms more straight forward.
    - Path generation should now consistently have a destination; no more paths to nowhere.
    - 'Corridor' not 'Cooridor'. Lots of comments were spelling this wrong- should have been using spellcheck.
    - Reconfigured staircase placement to allow for specific coordinates; again, to help with reading from file.
    - Created 'room_list', which is essentially just a linked list to store rooms dynamically. This will allow
      theoretically unlimited number of rooms. Updated Makefile accordingly.
02/09/2025
    - Fixed bugs with room_list. In the interest of time, I'm going to wait on actually using this
      in dungeon.c; main goal here is reading/writing, and room_list solves a minor bug with that.
02/10/2025
    - Created basic bit to randomly place player character when generating dungeon
    - Created methods for writing / reading to / from binary file; heavily work in progress.
    - Converted my array of int for rooms to room_list for dynamic allocation.
    - Created basic commandline arg parsing for --load and --save; or both, if that's your thing.
02/11/2025
    - Macgyver'd room_list to dynamically store locations for staircases (didn't think about it until now).
    - Continued work on implementing --load and --save
02/12/2025
    - Fixed small bug where some parts of corridor generation were not changing hardness to 0
    - Finished implementation of --load and --save, as well as the combination of the two
    - Changed filepath to work accross different users
    - v1.02 complete
